You can take a dump of your mysql and programmatically run it to restore the sql.the below code will restore the dump into sql.

    Runtime rt = Runtime.getRuntime();
    Process pr = rt.exec(&quot;mysql -p -h ServerName DbName &lt; dump.sql&quot;);

to take the dump please follow the below link [dump][1]


  [1]: https://blog.winhost.com/using-mysqldump-to-backup-and-restore-your-mysql-databasetables/

First, you need to export your database:

    mysqldump -u &lt;yourusername&gt; -p&lt;yourpassword&gt; &lt;yourdb&gt; &gt; &lt;yourfilepath&gt;

And then on the other computer importing the database will be needed:

    mysql -u &lt;yourusername&gt; -p&lt;yourpassword&gt; &lt;yourdb&gt; &lt; &lt;yourfilepath&gt;

