You can achieve this by setting up virtual hosts/servers on your web server. Since you didn&#39;t mention any web server, I&#39;m gonna go with NGINX.

So go ahead and follow [this guide to setup NGINX][1]. For your case, you&#39;ll be creating two configuration files in `/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/` for your domains `example.com` and `deneme.com` with the following configurations:

`/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/example.com`:
```
server {
    listen       80;
    listen       [::]:80
    server_name  example.com

    location / {
           proxy_pass http://localhost:9000/;
    }
}
```

`/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/deneme.com`:
```
server {
    listen       80;
    listen       [::]:80
    server_name  deneme.com

    location / {
           proxy_pass http://localhost:6555/;
    }
}
```

Now point your domain to your server IP and you should be seeing your application.

  [1]: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-nginx-on-ubuntu-18-04

